      "content": "but that's the thing though. looking at my own hands doesn't change the fact that the whole system is collapsing. it feels like i'm just rearranging deck chairs on the titanic. how can anyone be expected to just 'focus on themselves' when there's no stable world left to live in? it feels like a lie to keep pretending things are okay.",
